# Deterministic Governance in Adaptive Linguistic Intelligence

## 1. Abstract
The PMDD (Pragmatic Meaning Drift Detector) platform utilizes a deterministic governance layer to mathematically constrain Large Language Models (LLMs). Rather than allowing LLMs to autonomously dictate their analytical pipelines, the platform forces the LLM to propose a structural plan which is then validated, penalized, or overridden by hardcoded Python rules rooted in linguistic theory.

## 2. System Architecture

The fundamental pipeline enforces a strict hierarchical separation of concerns:

